value.0: A small man with calloused hands and tired eyes. He makes conversation with the barkeep and other patrons, happy to take in an ale after a long day's work.
A copy of this item (including any crafting you do on it) is used by your Bottled Companion.

Value.value: Harvests just ain't like they used ta' be.

value.0: A middle-aged man, muscular of build and great of beard. Brant works as the innkeep and is quick with a story for any situation.
This weary traveler is dressed a bit more flamboyantly than some of the locals.

Value.value: Long roads eventually lead to cozy stops.

value.0: A handyman and laborer evidently taking a rest from his work.

Value.value: Help yerself, mate, the foods' free! 'Leastwise the stew anyhow.

value.0: This grey-haired woman keeps to herself, enjoying a bit of stew from the hearth.
Though her hair has started to grey, the woman's warm smile and soft voice make her a timeless beauty.

There is nothing like a meal of grilled meat and steaming vegetables, heaped high upon the plate, to quell the most ravenous of hungers.

The stew is regularly fed with leftover vegetables and scraps of meat by the town's farmers and grocers. While the quality and tastiness varies between scoops, it's filling and free to take - though traditionally reserved for the poor and seasonal labourers.
